<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sad-adj">sad <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sæd/    美 /sæd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>难过的；令人悲痛的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was <strong>sad about</strong> the friends I was leaving behind. 
要离开这些朋友，我感到很难过。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The reporter thinks <strong>it is</strong> very <strong>sad that</strong> old trees will be burnt. 
记者认为要把古树烧掉令人十分痛心。</p><footer>译林⑤ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>糟透的；坏透的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A sad accident happened. 
发生了一起惨祸。</p></div></div>